<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1991) - "SOLID STATE" GLOW PLUG ANALYSIS GUIDE - "SOLID STATE" GLOW
        PLUG SYSTEM REPLACEMENT PROCEDURES - REMOVAL AND REASSEMBLY (Glow Plugs)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REMOVAL AND REASSEMBLY (Glow Plugs)</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the harness from the glow plug terminal(s), Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600637">6.37</hotlnk>. Use the 3/8" deep well socket to remove the glow plug. Using
                this deep socket provides the necessary clearance to allow the glow plug to be removed or installed
                without damaging the glow plug terminal.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4600637" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg10720" filename="../figcg1/CG10720.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.37 Glow Plug Harness</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the glow plug from the bore in the cylinder head, as shown in Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600638">6.38</hotlnk>. Install a new glow plug into the bore, as required, using a
                3/8" deep well socket. Tighten the glow plug to 12 lbf-ft. (16 Nm).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>It is not required to remove the glow plug harness and control unit prior to removing the glow
                        plugs.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4600638" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12410" filename="../figcg1/CG12410.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.38 Glow Plug Removal</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">* - Manual specified with latest revision</emph>
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
